{
  "stem": "1343.2",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But before they got off, there was a puddle of water-- it was after a rain-- so they yelled something, and, in a few minutes, a few people brought out a few Sefer Torahs, rolled them out, and the German, with his shining boots was walking out.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I remembered-- that time came back to my mind, that picture, when the Torah fell out in the shul.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I thought that the sky will open, thunder and lightning will strike these guys because they were walking on the Sefer Torah.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So at that point, I lost a little bit from my security of believing in--",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I just brought this up as an incident how people become face to face with, where is God?",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And is there any God?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And if there is, why isn't he reacting?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So anyhow, after the six months-- Wait.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I have to find out about the pneumonia.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was healed from the pneumonia, except there is some-- --deposits, that I almost lost my ability to come to America, because they were afraid of TB, you know.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But it was--",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In [NON-ENGLISH], they took me.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were far away from it when we were sleeping in our circles, but they took me into the city, where they gave me quinine-- quinine.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "This is-- before penicillin, this was the most effective, and that was unavailable for Jews, of course.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And that took down the fever, and I got back to my work within a week or so, or less.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So-- and this lasted until October, actually, 1944, when Szalasi, the Hungarian Nazi, came to power.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "You know the story that Horthy, the regent of Hungary, declared peace, and the same day the Hungarian Nazi party came to power.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
